<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>My question is...</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Malark">Malark</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 10:35 a.m. 4/5/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> My question is...<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=2015" TARGET=_self>Quick Clarification (must read for Necros)</A> (Geiger)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>My question is are they just saying that without fixing it or are they FIXING it? If they are saying to hold on and not use it because they are tirelessly working on a solution then I'm good with that (not please, nothappy, but I can deal). If they are just saying "No, don't use it, ever..." then I have a problem.

<P>Also what's the point of invising the pet if they can't use it to attack you anyway? Its illegal currently right? ;) Plus they fixed that recently did they not?
<P>My point is balancing isn't terribly an issue at the moment for me, its more of being able to use ALL of my skills in combat. Let's get the real horrible errors out of the way first (inability to use DoT in combat, pets, Specialization, Poison for Rogues, etc) then they can start looking for inconsistencies in game balance.
<P>In my opinion they shouldn't be balanced a lot anyway. Some classes SHOULD be better at combat. Magicians shouldn't be able to hold off wizards and NEcromancers, they have a great responsibility in the background and support, just like a cleric. Rogues shouldn't be on the front, they should try to sneak in for a backstab then run away, waiting for another opportunity. Maybe I'm being optimistic too.
<P>Malark
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
